only American not to advance from the first round,Brandon Miller, leads 400 at 50.2.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2153, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_Miller_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.5149247209662544, \"rank\": 0.4057971014490595, \"text\": \"Brandon Miller\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_Miller_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_Miller_(basketball)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He gets it done with the fastest split of the day in 1:44.21, a nice display of frontrunning.\", \"from\": 2188, \"to\": 2281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind himMohamed Ali Gouanedof Algeria andTobias Gronstadof Norway both PB in 1:44.37 and 1:44.57 to notch both time qualifiers.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad_Ali\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.6325391244696986e-18, \"text\": \"Ali\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad_Ali\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Muhammad_Ali\"}, {\"begin\": 2355, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"score\": 0.9995228725020673, \"rank\": 0.00047735447946189476, \"text\": \"PB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Byte\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's team will beChristian Coleman,Fred Kerley,Kyree King, andCourtney Lindsey.\", \"from\": 2413, \"to\": 2497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2453, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Kerley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\"}, {\"begin\": 2465, \"end\"